  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `v1.10.19`\r\nOS & Version: MacOS\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThe typed-data signing feature of Go Ethereum should work when the data is valid\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThe typed-data signing feature fails to encode the data. The reason is that casting `[]map[string]interface{}` to `[]interface{}` [here](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/4c114af5024943a7471aeccdf5e536584c1e21b4/signer/core/apitypes/types.go#L370) is not valid.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n```go\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\r\n\t\"fmt\"\r\n\r\n\t\"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/common/math\"\r\n\tethCrypto \"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/crypto\"\r\n\t\"github.com/ethersphere/bee/pkg/crypto\"\r\n\t\"github.com/ethersphere/bee/pkg/crypto/eip712\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\tprivateKey, _ := ethCrypto.HexToECDSA(\"<my-private-key>\")\r\n\tsigner := crypto.NewDefaultSigner(privateKey)\r\n\tmessageToSign := eip712.TypedData{\r\n\t\tDomain: eip712.TypedDataDomain{\r\n\t\t\tName:              \"ABC\",\r\n\t\t\tVersion:           \"0.0.1\",\r\n\t\t\tChainId:           math.NewHexOrDecimal256(1),\r\n\t\t\tVerifyingContract: \"<my-smart-contract-address>\",\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t\tTypes: eip712.Types{\r\n\t\t\t\"EIP712Domain\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t{Name: \"name\", Type: \"string\"},\r\n\t\t\t\t{Name: \"version\", Type: \"string\"},\r\n\t\t\t\t{Name: \"chainId\", Type: \"uint256\"},\r\n\t\t\t\t{Name: \"verifyingContract\", Type: \"address\"},\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\t\"MainType\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t{Name: \"items\", Type: \"Item[]\"},\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\t\"Item\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t{Name: \"itemType\", Type: \"uint8\"},\r\n\t\t\t\t{Name: \"itemName\", Type: \"string\"},\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t\tPrimaryType: \"MainType\",\r\n\t\tMessage: eip712.TypedDataMessage{\r\n\t\t\t\"items\": []eip712.TypedDataMessage{\r\n\t\t\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"itemType\":             math.NewHexOrDecimal256(2),\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"itemName\":                \"<item-name>\",\r\n\t\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tsignature, err := signer.SignTypedData(&messageToSign)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"Failed to sign typed data\", err)\r\n\t\treturn\r\n\t}\r\n\tfmt.Println(\"Signature\", hex.EncodeToString(signature))\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nError:\r\n```\r\nFailed to sign typed data provided data '[map[...]]' doesn't match type 'Item[]'\r\n```",
